posts.caption:
Leaning into your dreams is a powerful journey of self-discovery and resilience.

I used to feel so disconnected from the abuse I went through and having my brother in prison. Those struggles fueled my determination to become big and strong, a shield against the hurts of the past.

Achieving All-American status in sports seemed like the answer, but it left me with a deep sense of darkness.

The turning point? Letting go. Letting go of the stories, the pain, and embracing what truly moves you forward.Listen to your heart, lean into your dreams, and watch how the right path unfolds. üôèüèº

Drop a YES if this resonates, and always remember that you are loved, you are worthy, and you matter. üß°

posts.caption:
Your purpose is not what you do. It‚Äôs how you make others feel. Do you agree? Leave a ‚ÄúYES‚Äù below and I‚Äôll send you a link to my latest solo on The School of Greatness podcast üôè

Sometimes we get caught up in what we do as our identity and purpose but that can be a trap.

If the business fails, You are a failure. 

If the relationships ends, You are alone. 

If you get fired from the job, you are a loser. 

Don‚Äôt tie what you do into who you are in your heart. You are more than that. You are a gift to this world and it‚Äôs your choice on how you show up with the people around you. 

Hope this reminds you that every moment matters and even if you aren‚Äôt DOING exactly what you want in this season of life, everything can change in a moment based on how you make people feel.

posts.caption:
I am speechless.

I have been waiting for this moment for my entire adult life.

Last week, I met @oprah and she absolutely blew me away. Truly.

It was one of the single, defining moments of my life. And I will cherish the experience forever.

I am still trying to find the words to describe what it was like to finally meet the person I admire more than any other human being on this planet.

Oprah made me believe in a bigger vision for my life. Her TV show, magazine @oprahdaily, book club @oprahsbookclub, books, and movies provided the tools, wisdom, and inspiration that helped me do it.

Thank you Oprah for seeing me and inviting me to be on your new podcast. Thank you for all that you do for the world. Thank you for starting The Oprah Podcast. And thank you for reading my book.

I am speechless.

Thankfully, I have something better than words. I have an invitation for you.

Please join me and @oprah and take a moment to listen to or watch our conversation on The Oprah Podcast.

You can listen to it where ever you listen to podcasts or watch it on YouTube.com/@Oprah

This is one of the most important moments of my life and it is an honor to be able to share it with you. ‚ù§Ô∏è

posts.caption:
This clip was taken during the 4x4x48 Challenge in 2022 when we went around to different cities and ran a 4 mile route with an open invitation to anyone who wanted to join. 

The event was free and the turnouts were amazing and humbling. 

That said, we are thinking about doing something similar again where we travel around to different cities and do a 4-6 mile run in each location. It would not necessarily be part of a 4x4x48, just a run with a meet and greet.

We are only in the early stages of planning but wanted to open it up for feedback in terms of cities with interest, venues that might work for crowds of a few thousand people, volunteers, etc.

My only requirement is that you come and bring the energy! I will come for free. 

Please use the comments below to share your feedback and stay tuned!

posts.caption:
I believe 90% of you truly get it. Sadly, it is the 10% of you that are sprinkled throughout the world that infect a lot of people‚Äôs minds. 

A lot of people out here are taking on a very daunting task and when that task gets difficult, some of you 10%ers show up and fuck up that person‚Äôs drive and determination. 

You show them the path of least resistance and, in doing so, hurt their chances of succeeding at the very thing at which they wanted to succeed.

It was truly amazing to see some of the comments about a 10 second video of my feet. My balance was in question. Even my faith was questioned. It‚Äôs amazing how judged a person can be on a 10 second video of some feet. This is exactly why I don‚Äôt judge people. There is a lot more going on than what anyone can possibly see, especially in a 10 second clip. 

Now let‚Äôs get down to the real shit. True effort most times does not look pretty. Most times it takes all that you have and then some. You will come out bruised, blistered, and calloused and if you survived that effort to get to the other side of whatever it is, a new you is born. 

Some of you truly misinterpret the message that I put out and cloud it with your weakness. At the end of the day, all I am saying is if you can take one more step, no matter how bad the shit hurts, take that motherfucking step. 

We are all better than what we think we are! 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
Charlie Kirk: bold, fearless, unapologetic. 

You didn‚Äôt play small. You didn‚Äôt shrink to fit the mold. You went all out on your beliefs every single day.

Charlie didn‚Äôt wait for permission. He didn‚Äôt ask for validation. He stood up in a world that rewards silence ‚Äî and he spoke LOUD. 

Whether you agreed with him or not‚Ä¶ you heard him. You felt him. And that‚Äôs what legacy is about.

He was a young guy with a big mission. He didn‚Äôt wait for the world to change, he pushed it.

I respected his hustle, his conviction, and his courage. And while the world debates, complains, and watches from the sidelines, Charlie played full out.

Rest easy, brother. The fight continues, and your voice echoes louder than ever.

GC

posts.caption:
I was blessed to have this very special moment on stage with my mom, my daughters, and our aiga (family) ‚Äî dancing our Samoan culture‚Äôs sacred dance, the Taualuga. 

It‚Äôs custom for Samoan men to take their shirts off to proudly show our Polynesian tatau (tattoo) and the intricate stories our ink tells. 
Also custom for Samoan women to lift their lava lavas up to proudly show their beautiful malu (tattoo) on their legs as well. 

I‚Äôm slapping the ground as a way to show my respect for how significant this is and how SACRED our ground becomes in this moment with our elders (and my daughters dancing next to me). 

It‚Äôs emotional. 
You can‚Äôt help but feel it. 
The mana. 

Life is busy for everyone - so special moments like this mean the world to me, to honor our family, our culture and always so good coming back home to Hawaii. Yesaah ü§ôüèæ

 ‚ù§Ô∏èüå∫ü•É 

Shout to my fam, love you guys and let‚Äôs post up again soon! 
@maukawarriorsluau 
@tiana_nonosina 
@kay.faam 
@samoanstuntman

posts.caption:
Rest in Peace, Terry Bollea aka The Immortal Hulk Hogan üïäÔ∏èüíê 

To millions of little kids you were a childhood hero - myself included. 
In 1984, I gave you your ‚ÄúHULKSTER‚Äù headband back, in the locker room in Madison Square Garden - I was the lucky kid caught it when you threw it in the crowd. You were wrestling ‚ÄúMr Wonderful‚Äù, Paul Orndorff that night in the main event. You were shocked and so happy after the match because you told me that was your very last headband and if it weren‚Äôt for me, you‚Äôd have no way of getting that exact one made again. You promised me that you would get more made and give me a Hulkster headband of my own as a thank you gift. 

A month later in Madison Square Garden, you did just that. You kept your word, with a handshake and a ‚Äúthanks kid‚Äù. 
And that meant the world to that little 12 year old boy. 

Just 17 years later, and still a kid at the age of 29 years old ‚Äî I‚Äôm standing in the middle of the ring and facing you - one of my wrestling heroes in the main event of WRESTLEMANIA. 

The match was to decide who would go down in history, as The Greatest of All Time. 

When you kick out of my Rock Bottom finisher - just listen and FEEL that crowd go ELECTRIC‚Ä¶
all for you. I‚Äôve never felt anything like that in my entire wrestling career. It takes two to tango, but that historic crowd reaction was all for you. 

You may have ‚Äúpassed the torch‚Äù to me that night, but you, my friend‚Ä¶. 

‚Ä¶ you ‚Äúdrew the house‚Äù meaning you sold out every arena and stadium across the country in your prime as Hulk Hogan, on your way to becoming the greatest of all time. 

From deep in my bones, and on behalf of this wild and crazy world of professional wrestling that we love, I say to you now, and forever‚Ä¶

Thank you for the house, brother‚Ä¶ 

Thank you, for the house. 

RIP Terry Bollea aka Hulk Hogan üïäÔ∏è 

#goat 

üéûÔ∏è @thecarefreeworld @jonbrandoncruz

posts.caption:
A personal inside look at The Smashing Machine. 

Never expected this to happen, but this film has changed my life and illuminated parts of me I didn‚Äôt know existed. 
Very freeing for me. 

Emily‚Äôs performance in this film absolutely shakes your soul. She‚Äôs the heartbreaking truth that the loved ones of fighters, often sacrifice themselves too. 

Our writer & director, @bowedtie Benny Safdie provided a singularly inspired, and safe place for us to go raw, take flight, transform, and eventually- a hard landing. Thank you Benny. 

In the end, you realize that true self-acceptance - and being at peace with who you are - can be life‚Äôs biggest win. 

The Smashing Machine 
@a24 

In theaters October 3rd

posts.caption:
That look only a mom can give when I say ‚Äúyes, all twelve of my kids‚Äù üëÄ üòÇ

Had an awesome outside breakfast with my mom, back home here in Hawaii - just ‚Äútalking story‚Äù and having fun. Eventually, our talks will always lead to something sentimental, like how good for the soul it is to come back home, visit the graves of our family, and all that being home represents over the years. Family, culture, struggle, pride, humility, resilience, and mana. My mom came to Hawaii from Samoa when she was a kid and since then she has endured so much in her life. And as her son, I‚Äôm super grateful that she gets to experience her life these days come full circle ‚≠ïÔ∏è 

If you got a mama, make sure you bear hug today, make her laugh, and when she gets emo - see if she offers YOU some water
 üòÇü•π‚ù§Ô∏è 

The real rock of the family. 

#moms

posts.caption:
Had the great pleasure of spending time ‚Äì and playing chess ‚Äì with the delightful Ebs @Eze this week at the beautiful @sonbunyola in Mallorca. It is the most beautiful of properties on the island with the most delightful team working there (thank you all). 
 
Ebs of course scored the winning goal in Crystal Palace‚Äôs historic FA Cup victory, and is one of England‚Äôs brightest stars. He also wore a special classic @VirginAtlantic 90s jersey for the celebration parade, movingly paying tribute to a Palace-supporting family.
 
When I then heard he is also a huge chess fan, I invited him to come and give me a game (or five!)
 
We had four very entertaining games, which finished 2-2. Then in the deciding game, I very foolishly got my queen trapped‚Ä¶ Ebs should have guessed what was coming next!
 
Seeing as Ebs won a chess tournament recently, I‚Äôm not too disappointed. And we were thrilled to spend time with Ebs and his delightful wife Naima - we‚Äôve became firm friends. 
 
Best of luck for the season ahead, and I‚Äôll get you on the chessboard next time!

posts.caption:
Laziness is running rampant in this world. Perfect example, I just got through doing my long run today and I pull my car up to valet after the run. The two guys at valet saw me pull in while eating their In-N-Out burgers and decided it was too cold outside and that they preferred to finish their burgers rather than do their job. So I proceeded to do their job for them. 

When I was coming up, I had this thing called a conscience. Some of you don‚Äôt know what that is. So let me explain it to you. It‚Äôs a little voice in the back of your fucking head that tells you when you are being a little bitch, being lazy, being weak, making excuses, etc., and it makes you do the shit that you don‚Äôt want to do but you know it is the right thing to do. Back in the day there were consequences when you didn‚Äôt do what you were expected to do. 

I have been doing this shit and living this lifestyle for many many many years, long before social media. 

When this video was filmed back in 2009, the hard work, discipline and sacrifice were considered admirable and inspiring. Fast forward to 2024, and people now say I am obsessed, have mental issues, etc. 

Back in the day, I would show up to these ultra races with a stone cold, focused face, that was often described as ‚Äúa man on a mission.‚Äù Now, I show up with the exact same stone cold, focused face and I am said to be an unfriendly, unapproachable dick. Hence the reason why now I do my ultra races alone because it was never about to recognition in the first place, it was about the growth. 

Amazing how the times have changed! I am the same motherfucker I have always been. Times may change but I sure as fuck won‚Äôt! 

That‚Äôs why at damn near 50 years old, my broke down, fucked up body and jacked up knees, can still serve up a fat ass plate of humble poe to a lot of motherfuckers half my age and healthy as fuck! 

If it‚Äôs not obvious enough already, this is exactly why it is so easy to be great nowadays!  Stay hard!

posts.caption:
Whatever is in front of you, don‚Äôt put your head down, face it head on. Life is not going to give you any breaks.

The majority of us have been broken at least once in our lives. We can be broken spiritually, physically, emotionally, etc. 

If you have been broken once, you know exactly what it feels like. There is nothing unknown about the emotions, the pain, etc., that come with it. 

Many people try to avoid suffering- and I am not just talking about physical suffering (although they do try to avoid that too!)- but, suffering is inevitable in life. Suffering has no expiration date! 

Some of you disagree with my message and what I say, and that is fine. But there‚Äôs one thing you must do in life‚Ä¶you must always fight! Regardless of the odds, the circumstances, or the likelihood of coming up short, you must always fight! 

You may be injured, you may have failed, you may have been passed over for the promotion, and cut from the team, that does not mean you are broken! It just means you are being tested.

The response you need to have moving forward is ‚Äútry to break me again, motherfucker!‚Äù

Stay hard!

If you have been broken once, you know exactly what it feels like. There is nothing unknown about the emotions, the pain, etc., that come with it. 

Many people try to avoid suffering- and I am not just talking about physical suffering (although they do try to avoid that too!)- but, suffering is inevitable in life. Suffering has no expiration date! 

Some of you disagree with my message and what I say, and that is fine. But there‚Äôs one thing you must do in life‚Ä¶you must always fight! Regardless of the odds, the circumstances, or the likelihood of coming up short, you must always fight! 

You may be injured, you may have failed, you may have been passed over for the promotion, and cut from the team, that does not mean you are broken! It just means you are being tested.

The response you need to have moving forward is ‚Äútry to break me again, motherfucker!‚Äù

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
There have been more times in my life than I can count when I thought I was done, it was over, I had nothing left to give.  Whether it was from fatigue, or I was in my head, injuries, etc., BUT there was always more to give and always more to find. 

For those of you who have quit like I have in the past, you realize once you have quit that in face you did have more to give. It is those people who are able to find more even under the harshest conditions who succeed. 

We live in a world where people want to see you fail, many of you may disagree with that statement, oh but I know all too well! When you are on top of a mountain, people want to push you off! They are waiting for your mistakes. They are waiting for the moment when you can‚Äôt take another step. They are smiling at your failure. 

For those people who want to see you fail, what they don‚Äôt understand is this‚Ä¶ they are at the bottom of the mountain where there is tons of oxygen which allows them to run their mouth. 

For those few who have the guts to climb, the higher you climb, the less oxygen there is which means the less you talk. The air gets thin the higher you guy so you make a conscious choice to conserve your energy knowing that you want to get to the top of the mountain. And the air at the top of that mountain is very thin. Very little needs to be said while you are climbing the mountain let alone standing at the top! 

Remember this: all those days you don‚Äôt want to do something, all those days where injury plagues your mind and all those days when fatigue is keeping you in bed, you, my friend, are making a motherfucker happy by giving in to those feelings. 

This video captures a proud moment for me because 99% of my life, I have been fighting the voice of ‚Äújust stop, you don‚Äôt need to do this today!‚Äù I didn‚Äôt set out for awards. recognition, fame or success, I was simply trying to change how I felt about myself. 

So you all out there who are waiting for me to fail, you will see it, because I will continue to try and remember this too‚Ä¶.I don‚Äôt know who the fuck you are but you know who I am! 

P.S. This was at my induction to the International Sports Hall of Fame.

posts.caption:
CONTROLLING THE MULTI-VOICE DIALOGUE IN YOUR MIND‚Ä¢
-
This is an excerpt from the Huberman Lab podcast out now with @davidgoggins 
-
It‚Äôs a brutally direct, mechanistic and actionable discussion about how to embrace, confront and control the dialogue in your mind‚Äî paying specific attention to the negative voices as a way to transmute all that into successful real world behavior. Daily.
-
One thing is made clear: there is no way to avoid internal agony if your goal is to be the ultimate version of yourself.
-
The good news is that anyone can do it but that it requires going inward. Over and over again. David explains how. 
-
He also explains how people get distracted by the observable things in others‚Äî choosing to point their fingers at others, criticize, focus on hacks, etc as a way to avoid doing the real INTERNAL work for themselves. 
-
The episode is a roadmap that anyone can apply to better themselves but only if they are willing to embrace the full reality of their deepest self doubts, fears, shame and darkness. As David explains, that‚Äôs the basement and the place from where true growth starts.
-
You can find the episode in all formats by going to hubermanlab.com It‚Äôs timestamped so you can navigate quickly to the topics most of interest to you. 
-
Meanwhile, put any questions you may have in the comments section below this post and as always, thank you for your interest in science!
-
@davidgoggins @hubermanlab @stanford.med @stanford 
-
#neuroscience #science #neuroplasticity #voicesinmyhead

posts.caption:
One of the best jobs in the world and I am proud to be a part of it! 

This is my brother from Alaska,  Special K, jumping a fire and I was on deck to go next. 

With only a couple of weeks left in the jumping season, I thought it would be appropriate to share this video. We make it a point to have some fun right before each one of us gets in the door to jump. 

People always think I am so serious but I can clown with the best of them! When you are pushing the edge in life, it‚Äôs very important that in your toolbox you also have humor, laughter and some jokes to bring some levity to the situation! 

As you can see in the video, what lies beneath us isn‚Äôt some flat manicured field rather a dense forest filled with tall timber  and boulders, etc. You never know for sure what exactly you are going to encounter once you hit the ground. The only guarantee is that there will be a shit ton of hard labor to be done by very few people. Some of the hardest working individuals I know!

And‚Ä¶22 is a reference to the year we both rookied. 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
In life, you will figure out own thing. When you are trying to make something of yourself, you will have more bad days than good. 

That is the separator of those who make it and those who don‚Äôt. A person who is able to function at a high level on bad days will make it far in life. 

The problem is that most people can‚Äôt consistently perform on those bad days. 

What I came to realize is that my life was full of very bad days so I had to learn to perfect the conquerer‚Äôs mindset. 

The conqueror‚Äôs mindset is like this- a conquerer doesn‚Äôt care what is going on in life. A conquerer knows that life is always going to bring challenges. 

It is how we handle those challenges that determines where we end up in life. 

Like it or not, it must be done. 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
Very few people know what you have gone through, what you are going through, or just how fucked up your life has been! 

Some of us have experienced extreme hardships. These hardships may make us talk a certain way, act a certain way or  even look a certain way. 

I learned a long time ago to never judge a person. There are a lot of things I want to say to people but I quickly pull back because I don‚Äôt know what led them to who and where they are now in life. 

That said, there are a lot of judgey-motherfuckers out here in this world today! 

If you do something that they don‚Äôt like or if your opinion doesn‚Äôt align with theirs (and countless other examples I could use!), they quickly want to get on social media or when they see you, they want to get in your face for not doing or saying exactly what they want to hear, etc. 

If you are a person who does that, more power to you. BUT‚Ä¶you opened the door for a big can of Go-Fuck-Yourself! 

The very person who you are judging or looking down on for whatever reason just might dislike you even more than you dislike them! They just chose to kept their mouth shut because it served no point to verbalize their unsolicited opinion. I can guarantee you this, a lot of people hope you say something to them just so they can go the fuck off and say something right back to your ass. 

I happen to be one of those people and this man gave me the perfect opportunity to share with him my opinion and exactly what I thought of him. While my feelings were not hurt because I have become calloused to it, I could tell that he was taken aback by my truth to him. 

While it is great to have an opinion and stand for something, you best be sure your shit is tight before you verbalize it. It might be best in life when you have an opinion to either shut the fuck up or look at yourself real hard in the mirror before you open your fucking mouth. The return blows that you will receive might just be a lot more damaging than the ones you threw! 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
Who you surround yourself with matters! That foxhole mentality that I talk about is a real thing. 

You want to be around people who challenge you to the core of your soul and make you find more of yourself when you believe you have no more left. 

This fire season was a challenging one- it was the busiest fire season in BC history- which also meant that a lot of people didn‚Äôt get to work out the way to which they are accustomed. That said, when I put out the challenge for people to end the smokejumping season with a 50k Ruck just about every smokejumper signed up to take on the challenge. It‚Äôs speaks volumes about the culture and character of the Jumpers here in British Columbia,  @smokejumpers_bc 

It‚Äôs important that we always press up against our perceived limits. You learn nothing about yourself when you always do the things within your known limits. 

It is only when we press tightly against those edges that we expand our limited horizons and understanding of what‚Äôs truly possible. 

The question that we must all ask ourselves is ‚Äúwhat am I actually capable of?‚Äù It is so much more than what you think. 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
The road to success isn‚Äôt always a clear and smooth path. We are all being tested in life and those tests aren‚Äôt easy for any of us. 

Many people assume I go into things without thinking but it is quite contrary. 

When I finally pulled my head out of my ass and realized what I truly wanted in life, I had to sit back and think about what it would take for me to get there. I had to measure my want. 

What that means is I had to ask myself ‚ÄúWhat am I willing to put myself through to achieve it? What am I willing to give up in order to achieve it?‚Äù

I went all in on me. I knew that there would be a lot of bumps and bruises along the way. Some over-use injuries and a lot of dark times. But, for me, it was all worth it. My want was so great that I didn‚Äôt give a fuck what it came with. Sometimes your want isn‚Äôt that great and doesn‚Äôt warrant that kind of dedication. 

It makes some people feel good to think that I‚Äôm all fucked up. It‚Äôs almost like I-told-you-so type shit. See, he ran too much, didn‚Äôt rest enough, etc. While my body is fucked up and I have had my fair share of injuries, I‚Äôve always worked myself back and my body still works better than most healthy bodies because my mind is trained different than most. 

Too many people talk too much about giving yourself a break. More people need to talk about giving more and pushing harder.  20 years ago, people would see my effort as ‚ÄúDamn, that guy truly wants it bad!‚Äù Nowadays my effort is looked at, like, ‚ÄúLook at what he‚Äôs doing to himself?!‚Äù

Many of you haven‚Äôt found what you truly want in your life. Once you do, I suggest you figure out how to give your all.  No, I‚Äôm not saying fuck yourself up! There‚Äôs a very thin line in between we all must walk if we are looking for true greatness in ourselves. The real problem isn‚Äôt the fear of a fucked up body. It‚Äôs your fear of the effort required to truly give your all.

For many of us, we must be willing to live on that edge. Yes, you might die with a used up body but it will be a body that truly lived and conquered! 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
Tony finished Hell Week today. I have had many people try yet he is the first one to get through it. 

I have had a lot of great athletes over the years want to train with me but for one reason or another, ‚Äúsomething‚Äù
always miraculously comes up so they can‚Äôt complete it. 

There is a look I see on the faces of people who are on the brink of quitting called the thousand yard stare. They start asking questions- when is it going to end? what‚Äôs next? how many sets are left? are we coming back again tonight? is this healthy for you? 

This is when I usually start laughing my ass off. I tell them it is time to pack your bag and go home. Once you start asking these questions, I know you are not committed. 

I broke El Cucuy on Day One, or at least I thought I did. I had him deep in the hurt locker and figured the questions were soon to be coming. I told Kish late that night ‚Äúthis motherfucker is done!‚Äù

But, I was wrong. 

He woke up on Day Two even more fired up to go. There was never a question asked. His response was always the same ‚ÄúOK, Coach.‚Äù

Around 11pm on Wednesday night, when he could barely walk after having completed nearly 2 miles of walking lunges and a shit ton of other cardio and weight training, I figured I would put a fork in him and gut him. But the craziest thing happened‚Ä¶.

The motherfucker gave me a crazy ass smile and I could tell that he had flipped the switch. 
I was there for the rebirth of El Cucuy. 

It happened somewhere on the Jacob‚Äôs Ladder at around 11:11pm. I knew then that the torture I was putting him through was no longer torture. 

In order to get through hell, you have to become the Devil! And that night, the Devil surfaced and boy was it a beautiful sight to behold! 

We both laughed because we knew what was happening. 

A lot of people ask me if I think he will win his next fight- I don‚Äôt have the first damn clue about that. That‚Äôs up to Tony. 

What I do know is that the man who walks into the octagon on December 16th will be a deeply changed man. 

Sometimes when the fight is near, the warrior must go back home because home is where the hell began. 

My friends, Tony is home! Hello darkness my old friend.

posts.caption:
This message is for those people in search of a new realm and looking to leave normal behind. 

For those who are looking or are seeking a new realm in life, you have to be prepared for a lonely journey. 

Know that people will fall off. Friends and family aren‚Äôt going to be able to push you to the limits you need to be pushed. They simply won‚Äôt understand the journey you are on. 

Those people around you will see where their world ends and your world begins. You are willing to go that much further, dig that much deeper, endure that much more, and suffer that much longer. Your resolve needs to be that much deeper. Always, without fail. 

Before you go to bed at night, you must ask yourself just one question. Have I done enough today? If the answer is no, you must find it within yourself to forego sleep and be willing to go the extra mile. 

You must realize that if you are in search of finding that new realm, you must be willing to extend yourself to the limit without any guarantee of success. 

Be willing to be the one who is willing to sharpen your sword alone. 

Stay hard!

Know that people will fall off. Friends and family aren‚Äôt going to be able to push you to the limits you need to be pushed. They simply won‚Äôt understand the journey you are on. 

Those people around you will see where their world ends and your world begins. You are willing to go that much further, dig that much deeper, endure that much more, and suffer that much longer. Your resolve needs to be that much deeper. Always, without fail. 

Before you go to bed at night, you must ask yourself just one question. Have I done enough today? If the answer is no, you must find it within yourself to forego sleep and be willing to go the extra mile. 

You must realize that if you are in search of finding that new realm, you must be willing to extend yourself to the limit without any guarantee of success. 

Be willing to be the one who is willing to sharpen your sword alone. 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
I am not who I used to be‚Ä¶some might say I am a little bit better. While I am not as fast as I once was, my endurance of the mind is far superior to what it used to be. I know exactly where the mind is going to go before it goes there. 

This group of guys has been wanting to run with me for a long time so I got tired of them asking. While they say they want to run with me, I know they really want to kick my ass. That said, they committed a cardinal sin. I asked them how far they wanted to run when we were about 3 miles into the run. They saw I was limping to start and my gait was a little fucked up so I looked slow and old. So, their answer was ‚Äúas far as you want to go.‚Äù I simply replied ‚ÄúRoger that!‚Äù There is a start line to quitting and I know exactly where that starts and I am going to take all these motherfuckers there! 

Three things they didn‚Äôt know,  my knee is still trying to reset after surgery, hence the limp, and I don‚Äôt get warmed up or find my stride until about 45 minutes into my run. Last thing, when you see me wearing this black pack around my waist, it means you are in for a long fucking day! 

I found out a long time that when the distance is unknown, it truly fucks with people. As we got to about the 20 mile mark, they knew where we started and got a little happy as we were coming upon that starting point. When we continued to run past that starting point, their happiness turned to sadness. 

My limp was gone, my breathing was easy, and I knew they had to be thinking ‚Äúwe are running with a guy who can run 250 miles nonstop.‚Äù All that made me laugh inside as we passed what they thought was the finish line.

Never underestimate a person who trains every single day of their life. They might just know something you don‚Äôt! 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
Countless men and women fought for our freedom. Yes, I get it, some of you may not feel free because of how hard your life has been or how hard you have had to work but, you are free. Your life may suck, but you are free. We need to truly ask ourselves what are we doing with the freedom that we have? 

A lot of us are familiar with the talk about the economic recession. We, individually, have no control over that. But, a lot of you are not familiar with the mental recession a lot of people are experiencing. The mental recession is something that you can control. The mental recession is self-imposed. A lot of you are sitting around waiting for the world to come help you, bitching about how hard life is. You are a prisoner in your own mind! 

One thing I realized when I was a young kid living an abused life, was that I wasn‚Äôt the only abused kid. Once I realized that, it made things a lot easier to handle. There are a lot of people experiencing this mental recession and the sad thing about it is a lot of people choose to be there. Not only do they choose to be there, they choose to stay there rather than do the hard work necessary to get out. 

A lot of people who serve/served this country did not want to serve, they felt like they had to serve. When you live that way, you eliminate choices from your life. You don‚Äôt do only what you want to do rather do what you have to do.

Trust me when I was damn near 300lbs and at the bottom of the barrel, that took no effort at all. I could eat what I want, I had no expectations of myself, no standards to meet, no ambition, no goals or dreams keeping me up at night. That was the easy life. Looking back, it is amazing how many ‚Äúfriends‚Äù I had at that point in my life. 

The more I got out of my mental recession, the more the weight peeled off, the bigger the goals I set for myself, the more respect I gained for myself, the more my ‚Äúfriends‚Äù also peeled off. 

I want to thank all Veterans again for fighting for our freedom. It is truly up to us what we choose to do with that freedom. 

We can choose to let life just happen to us or attack life and go to war with ourselves! 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
Someone recently tagged me in this video.

When this man challenged me to an arm wrestling competition, he was comfortably seated in his chair. I could tell he was a massive man but when he stood up, he was literally a fucking giant.  He was a 6‚Äô7‚Äù 330lb former Offensive Tackle at OSU. 

I will never forget when I grabbed his hand, I remember thinking this must be what a bear‚Äôs paw feels like. 

The takeaway is this- he called me out in front of a room full of people and even though I don‚Äôt arm wrestle, I knew if I could just hang with him for a few seconds, I would get in his head. You know when a person challenges you to something, it is something that they are good at so I knew that he thought that he was going to destroy me but, as we all know, YOU DON‚ÄôT KNOW ME, SON!!!!

A lot of times all we have to do is create doubt in the opposition. That doubt takes away their confidence and levels the playing field which creates an opportunity on which to capitalize. If you are not sure you are going to win at something, make sure you stay in it long enough to make your opponent doubt themselves! 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
I know firsthand just how frustrating and unfair life can be. Many people are looking for help when times get bad and that is the right thing to do. But, if you expect people to want change and success for you as bad as you do, that is never going to happen. 

It is important that we take accountability for the actions that may have gotten us in to the situation that we are currently facing. 

I recognize that there are tons of things over which we have no control that contribute to the multitude of problems that people are facing in this world.
The challenge is that 99% of the people who may have helped to fuck you up, and may be partially to blame for the situation you are in, are not coming back to apologize and help fix you. The responsibility is solely on you. 

So getting mad at someone for not helping you the way you want to be helped, and when you want to be helped, is not going to help or solve the problem. 

Truth be told, while many people want to help you, it is still not their problem so if they see that you are not invested in yourself, they are definitely not going to want to invest in you.

There is only so much someone else can do for you anyway. Someone can give you tips and advice but, at the end of the day, if you are in school, they can‚Äôt take the test for you, if you are fat, they can‚Äôt lose the weight for you. 

Know this‚Ä¶.if I don‚Äôt get back to you lickety-split on your email, like I have said countless times before, there are just two people trying to respond to all of the emails. Instead of sending me a nasty email while awaiting my response, that time could have been better spent at the gym getting a workout in or meal-prepping for the week. 

And to the gentleman who wrote asking for help: You are right, I was fat and the thing that helped me out the most was my attitude. Being a victim only adds to the problem and delays the forward progress. 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
It‚Äôs so easy to be great nowadays.

A lot of people want to level up in this world simply because they think they deserve it or are entitled to it. 

For those who truly do want to level up, one of the best ways of doing it is by sometimes seeking out opportunities where misery is calling your name. 

The more miserable the task is in front of you, the harder you must become. This isn‚Äôt some macho bullshit, this is a proven tactic that works. So don‚Äôt wish it away, welcome its presence. When you stop thinking that something sucks, it does.

You shouldn‚Äôt want to be normal. The standard for normal in today‚Äôs world has changed. Normal is just the new word for weak. 

Don‚Äôt get it twisted - while I am talking about working out in the video, this definitely isn‚Äôt just about working out. 

Very few people go after anything anymore like there is no tomorrow. Those who do are the outliers and are often looked at or perceived as crazy. 

They are not crazy, they‚Äôre just not you. 

Like I always say, my message isn‚Äôt for everybody so if you get offended, I am not for you. I am for those people who are searching for greatness inside themselves. 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
As we all know, it is very important to set goals. Goals keep you focused and give you purpose. But, if you are always setting goals that you know you can achieve, there is very limited growth in that. 

If you are trying to maximize your growth, it is important that you set goals that may be outside of your reach. Setting audacious goals applies the pressure that your body and mind needs in order to grow as it forces you to find more. The fear, the doubt and the hard work necessary to achieve that goal are the very things that you need. 

If you are setting a goal that you already know you can achieve, is it really a goal? It should be just something on your to do list rather than your goal list. 

We are so afraid of failure that we always try to set ourselves up for success. So many negative things come with failure- feelings of not being good enough, you feel like you wasted your time, the naysayers talking their shit, etc.- it almost feels like it wasn‚Äôt even worth it. 

Oh but trust me, it is! If we didn‚Äôt have people out there who weren‚Äôt afraid of setting massive goals, we wouldn‚Äôt have half the shit we have today. Running the 4 minute mile, getting someone to the moon, flight, etc. 

Be the one willing to test the limits and not give a fuck in doing so! If your goal is to reach the stars, there is a good chance you won‚Äôt get there but just imagine how high you will get in attempting to do so! 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
It‚Äôs amazing how many people have no guilt & are totally emotionless when it comes finding more of themselves. They wake up, walk around, & go to bed with zero accountability. They can spend an entire day not working on improving themselves. Not because they physically or mentally couldn‚Äôt rather because they just didn‚Äôt want to. An entire day wasted & yet they are not thinking about the consequences & cumulative effect of wasted days. 

Since we can‚Äôt say shit in this world nor can we hold people accountable, we have morphed into a society where we just encourage everyone to be happy with who they are and the status quo. 

DON‚ÄôT TWIST MY MESSAGE- I am not saying to not be happy with you are. If there is something you literally CAN‚ÄôT improve through hard work & effort‚Ä¶ wait a minute, here I am now trying to explain what I mean so that I don‚Äôt offend people who are looking to be offended!!! 

The bottom line is this- no one is happy being behind the power curve in any situation in life but it has become very acceptable to ignore the voice of hard work and discipline. It is easy to ignore it because that it what society is pushing nowadays. 

In my life, I was behind the power curve in countless situations- my weight, my learning, my self-discipline, etc. Thank God I grew up in a generation that preached ‚Äúwork harder‚Äù rather than just accepting the cards that I was dealt. 

A lot of you are fucked nowadays because the message being preached is just the opposite. ‚ÄúThat‚Äôs just how you were born‚Äù- be happy about it rather than attempt to outwork it! Be happy just meeting the standard!

Just know that the very people who are preaching this to you and telling you that it is ok to be mediocre, are the very same people who will not hire you because they don‚Äôt want an underachiever on their team! They are just saying what they are told to say even though they don‚Äôt truly believe it. 

It‚Äôs easy to see why I am misunderstood by so many people because my message is almost obsolete nowadays. 

Many of you will continue to fail if you do not figure out how to do just because you need to do. No one gives a fuck what you want to do! 

Stay hard!

You know this is going to be one of my best friends for life when the first day we meet, he takes me out for a 35 mile race, a brutal gym workout, and teaches me how to shoot a bow all on Day 1 of friendship! 

@cameronrhanes is part of a small group of people- and when I say small, I mean VERY small! So many people out here are telling you to get up early, go hard, grind, get uncomfortable, and tons of other overused catch phrases. 

Most of them are full of shit. All you have to do is look at their out of shape bodies to see just how out of date their resumes are! 

I have been looking for decades for people who don‚Äôt use excuses like age, past successes, schedules, weather, etc., and truly love the Day One, Week One mentality. 

I have seen firsthand that Cam is one of them. Mad respect! 

Very few people push me to the point where I have to kill David Goggins and bring out Goggins!

posts.caption:
I am not talking about a mental condition here, it‚Äôs a mindset condition! 
 
Some of us are so used to doing exactly what we want to do when we want to do it that when we have to do the things we don‚Äôt want to do, those very things become impossible to do. 

You have to adjust your mindset to ignore those feelings of comfort when they come around. 

Some of you softer people out there may take that as me saying don‚Äôt ever be comfortable. I am not saying that. 

What I am saying is during those times when you have to grind, you must put comfort to the side. 

To repeat, when I say ‚Äúbitch‚Äù it is not gender-specific. It is a mindset that applies to those people who whine, feel sorry for themselves, act soft in times when they should be acting hard. I think you get the idea. 

And, if you are offended by this, you might be a bitch! 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
We all have that dog mentality. What happens to a lot of us though is that we stop feeding it. 

How you feed it is by continually putting obstacles in front of yourself. You must have goals. You can‚Äôt ever lose your ambition. You must always have an insatiable appetite for growth. 

Don‚Äôt ever allow yourself to get full! When you get full, you also get satisfied. And that can be the start of a very slippery slope! 

Don‚Äôt take this shit wrong, no one is saying not to rest or take days off‚Ä¶ what I am saying is not to rest too long and don‚Äôt take too many days off. The mind loves comfort! The more you stay in that zone, the harder it is to get out of it. 

We need all kind of people in this world. The savage is becoming extinct.

Stay hard!

That‚Äôs when you need to step back from whatever it is at which you are failing and realize that you missed it. 

What you missed is to see the person who is willing to continue to try despite failing. It says just the opposite of you being a failure! It shows your character, your determination, your will. The very traits that ultimately make you a success! 

Failure has a way of making you forget all of that and leaves you feeling like a loser who wants to stop trying altogether. 

Most people nowadays aren‚Äôt even putting themselves in the position to fail because they aren‚Äôt even trying so your failure may feel even more exposed. 

You need to get to the point in your life where you no longer look at it as failure rather see it merely as an attempt! 

You must remember this- the valiant motherfucker always wins even when the world around you may see you ‚Äúfailing.‚Äù

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
You don‚Äôt give yourself nearly enough credit.

Think about how hard you try every single day.

You get up, you handle your responsibilities, you push through the hard stuff, you show up for people, you keep going even when no one is cheering you on.

And yet, instead of celebrating that, you obsess over the one thing you didn‚Äôt get done. Or the one mistake you made.

It‚Äôs time to change that.

I want you to repeat this mantra every morning:

‚ÄúI need to give myself more credit for how hard I‚Äôm trying.‚Äù

Because the effort counts, even when the results aren‚Äôt here yet.

The hardest work you‚Äôre doing is often invisible, but it matters.

So today, stop waiting for someone else to notice and notice yourself.

In this episode of @themelrobbinspodcast, I‚Äôm teaching you how to train your brain to see more opportunity, focus on the positive, and get excited about your life again using research and proven affirmations.

Listen now! üéß ‚Äú8 Things To Tell Yourself Every Morning"

posts.caption:
Just a little insight into what it‚Äôs really like to live with David Goggins. 

I laugh when I see the comments that suggest his one minute videos are staged. I have logged thousands of miles alongside him and filmed almost every video while on foot so my body can also attest to the fact that every single video is legit and merely a one-minute snapshot of what each and every day brings! 

This video was captured as I was crewing him on a 100 mile ruck that, at 10am, was just an idea that came to fruition just a few hours later. 

Some people are not meant to be understood and David is one of them. He is one-of-one and I am grateful for the opportunity to grow and get better every day just by being in his presence.

posts.caption:
You don‚Äôt ever need to be understood by anybody as long as you know where the hell you are going! 

It‚Äôs funny how many people misunderstood me for so many years. It wasn‚Äôt until I became successful that it all started to make sense to them. 

Your journey in life is yours and yours alone. Be willing to look into the dark abyss  and have the coverage to take that step towards the darkness. 

When I was on Joe‚Äôs podcast he asked me how much I am going to miss running and all of the grinding and things I have done for decades now. When I answered the question by telling him that I won‚Äôt miss it at all, he was taken aback. 

You see we all have a limit to ourselves and I know I have far exceeded my limit. I exceeded that limit years ago. I pushed way past what I was thought was even possible for me. 

Now I wake up everyday and i‚Äôm still able to get after it- it is all just gravy to me poured on top of the fat ass meal I have already devoured. 

My goal in life was to find more when there was no more left to find. I managed to do that several times in my life. 

I am still misunderstood by many people and I truly understand why. We live in a world where most people don‚Äôt push themselves at all let alone to their limits and beyond. 

The day will come when many of you will have time to reflect back on your life and there will be many gaps of effort that you will be able to easily remember and, for some of you, it will make you feel a certain way. 

For many of you it will be a lot of regret and disappointment and questioning what could have been. 

I speak from experience. I had those exact same feelings and felt worthless and as if life has passed me by.

The only difference is that I was 24 years old and had time to make a change in my life. If you have this conversation with yourself too late, the regret will be permanent.  Only you know if you have truly given your all. 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
There is something that you need to get in your head. No one, and I mean no one, is ever going to feel sorry for you. There may be some people who sit there and appease you but there is very little that anyone can do for you. 

You and you alone are the only one who can get you out of your darkness. We often wonder why we can‚Äôt get out of the darkness that we are in. There is a simple answer to it- you are choosing to stay in it. 

I know your response to this is ‚ÄúI am trying, I am trying to get out of the darkness and find my better self.‚Äù Like most people, your trying is too inconsistent. Therefore the little gains that you made while you were trying, were likely all given back and then some due to your inconsistency. 

A lot of us are only disciplined when someone is in our face on a daily basis. We need that accountability person in our lives. The second they go away, we go away. 

A lot of you think it is ok to be where you are and society tells you as much, mediocrity is too often rewarded.

I am speaking from experience. It is hard to judge yourself nowadays and see where you stand and how you measure up because the world is grading us all on a massive curve. Like in school, the curve is off of the highest grade. The problem today is that the world is grading us on a ‚ÄúC-‚Äú curve, therefore a ‚ÄúD‚Äù doesn‚Äôt seem so bad! You think you are doing just fine. 

When I was lazy in school, living that mediocre life, when I got my ‚ÄúD‚Äôs‚Äù, I was happy because I knew a ‚ÄúD‚Äù was passing. That is how pathetic the standard was that I set for myself. The bar was so fucking low. 

As I look around me now, I see a lot of people happy with a ‚ÄúD‚Äù in life. 

Stay hard!

posts.caption:
Had a great conversation with my personal doctor and good buddy, @drmarkhyman. 

A lot of guys wait until something really goes wrong before they check in on their health. 

I didn‚Äôt want to be one of them.

I‚Äôve always tried to be a disciplined guy, and most days - I feel great. But something was off‚Äîand I couldn‚Äôt quite crack it.

I was introduced to Dr. Hyman through a mutual friend and discovered there‚Äôs a whole lot of value in being proactive, asking questions, digging deeper to uncover root causes and taking control of your own health. 

I‚Äôve always prioritized my fitness, my nutrition and my mental strength - those core things have been the anchor that allows me to do everything else I love to do - be creative, be a dad, have fun. But doing some of this comprehensive testing challenged what I thought ‚Äòhealth‚Äô looked like for me and it‚Äôs been a really encouraging and eye-opening experience. 

If any of this resonates with you - this conversation between myself and Dr. Hyman is for you. 

Enjoy and let me know your thoughts. 

Our episode of The Dr. Hyman Show is live now on YouTube and podcast platforms.

posts.caption:
A brotherly hug almost 10 years in the making ü´±üèæ‚Äçü´≤üèºü§éü§ç @jellyroll615 

Several years ago (roughly 2017) I was going through a very hard thing at the time, I was struggling. My mental wellness turned into my mental hellness. Many of you know the drill, you put on ‚Äúthe face‚Äù, show up to work, smile and get through it. 
Perhaps not the healthiest thing to do, but it‚Äôs what I was used to doing at the time. 

Then a song came on through my headphones one morning on a random shuffle playlist. ‚ÄúOnly‚Äù from Jelly Roll. 
The lyrics rocked me. 
Hard core. 

The words moved me so much that I reached out to Jelly. I said you don‚Äôt know me and I don‚Äôt know you, but this song of yours is helping me through some stuff I‚Äôm dealing with. I just called to say thank you brother. 

Our bond was born. 

The gift I gave Jelly when we finally met, is insignificant to the world, but something I just knew would mean a lot to him and he‚Äôd appreciate. It‚Äôs an old, and cheap postcard of a little motel called the Alamo Plaza in south Nashville. When I was 15yrs I was forced (family was evicted) to leave Hawaii and make it to Nashville to live with my dad. That didn‚Äôt work out so I wound up living with a stranger in this little spot on Murfreesboro Road that has since been torn down and no longer there. 

Downtown Bruno was that stranger‚Äôs name and to this day, he‚Äôs one of my best and most special friends. 

Just like Jelly. 
A very special friend. 

Every once in a while we all get sliced up by life, but it‚Äôs amazing to see what kind of blessings and people that God and the universe will put in our lives to help us heal through our pain. 

And a big SURREAL shout out to our boy @craigmorgan üé∂ who I was just listening to in my truck as I pulled up to meet Jelly. 

How‚Äôs THAT for the universe conspiring for us!! F#%king crazy ü§Ø 

Love you brother and cheers to all our plaques coming down. 

ü•É

Beautiful edit üé•‚ù§Ô∏è @jonbrandoncruz

posts.caption:
It‚Äôs not the win - it‚Äôs the PRESSURE TO WIN that can become our greatest heartache. 

It was my deepest honor to induct my brother, ‚ÄúThe Smashing Machine‚Äù @markkerrtsm into the 2025 @UFC Hall of Fame. 

Mark was one of the greatest fighters on the planet, and during that same time he overdosed twice as he battled his addictions outside of the cage. 

Today, Mark serves as a pillar of hope to everyone out there who‚Äôs holding onto faith, and battling their own demons - one day, one hour, one minute at a time. 

And what a difference one minute can make. 

Mark‚Äôs smile and laugh lights up the room, but it‚Äôs his humility, gratitude, and soft spoken kindness that makes him special. 

Pressure to win. 
Accountability when you don‚Äôt. 
Grace when it‚Äôs all over. 
Gratitude as new life begins. 

Love you brother and thank you for living your life - as your life, has changed mine. 

Mark ‚ÄúThe Smashing Machine‚Äù Kerr 
UFC Hall of Fame 
Class of 2025

This week on YAP, I‚Äôm joined by a real estate mogul and one of the most influential sales leaders in the world, Grant Cardone (@grantcardone), where he breaks down one of the biggest myths in sales: that being liked is the key to closing deals! ü§ù

üëâüèº trying to be overly nice

üëâüèº thinking that sales depend on how much they‚Äôre liked

An hour later, another one gets a buyout offer at 14x EBITDA. That's the ebb and flow of life and business. It took me years to figure it out, but now I cruise through it all, knowing bad stuff will pass, and good stuff will come. Wish l'd known this when I was 25.

posts.caption:
In 1999, I was barely able to run down the street. 

It‚Äôs amazing what we can do in a short period of time if we dedicate ourselves to getting better, finding more, and pushing further. 

It only took a few years for me to start unlocking my mind and discovering what I was capable of doing. The ability to push harder and go further is in all of us. All you need to do is be willing to test your perceived limits in order to unlock it. 

Stay hard!

This is Dyslexic Thinking at its best.
 
My advice to everyone pitching a business idea: Make sure you include stats, as well as a clear ask.
 
Even better if you can show that purpose doesn‚Äôt have to come at the expense of profit, like Beccy has here.
 
Great stuff.

posts.caption:
I didn‚Äôt know @aaronsingerman and I didn‚Äôt know about this featured clip from his podcast where I was used as clickbait until it was brought to my attention. 

This particular clip I am talking about got over 700k views on YouTube and I received a lot of embarrassing questions about it. 

As Gandhi says, silence becomes cowardice when occasion demands speaking out the whole truth so here is my opportunity. 

I called Aaron who had this one particular Navy SEAL on his show where they ran their mouths about me and asked him to have me on so that I can answer his questions, not with lies but with the facts of my military service record as well as some private DMs exchanged with this very same person proving that they talk out of both sides of their mouth. 

So unlike some of these bitches who have been running their mouths and lying, talking about how I never deployed, never went to combat, would go to military schools instead of combat, etc., I am taking it straight to them with the facts. I told @aaronsingerman to ask me whatever questions he had about me because he obviously heard a lot of negative things too in his dealing with members of the SEAL community. 

Sadly, a lot of these same people already know the truth and are purposefully lying to defame my name and character. 

I never wanted to bust some of these motherfuckers out but when you back a motherfucking dog into a corner, at some point, you are gonna piss him off. 

I have some supposed ‚Äúhero‚Äù from SEAL Team 6 DM‚Äôing people saying that I was dishonorably discharged from the military- which is a total lie- along with so many other lies. He didn‚Äôt know he was DM‚Äôing my lawyer!!! 

All of this will make perfect sense to you after you listen to this podcast.

A lot of these fraternities, like the SEALs, run in packs. When I found the truth out about a lot of them within the community, I decided to walk alone and this is the price I have paid.

posts.caption:
Watching my mother change drastically because of her Alzheimer‚Äôs disease was a confusing and painful experience. I learned that she had a separate but related condition called agitation in Alzheimer‚Äôs dementia.

To help others on their Alzheimer‚Äôs caregiver journey, the Alliance for Aging Research (@agingresearch) and I are raising awareness for agitation in Alzheimer‚Äôs dementia. 

If you have a loved one who lives with Alzheimer‚Äôs disease and starts showing signs of restlessness, yelling or resisting help, talk to their doctor. I wish I knew about agitation in Alzheimer‚Äôs dementia while I was caring for my mother.

If you‚Äôre caring for a loved one, you are not alone, and your dedication is meaningful and inspiring. ‚ù§Ô∏è

To learn more, visit www.AlzheimersAgitation.org. April 2025 11US25EUC0021

posts.caption:
This is the truth when it comes to chasing your dreams and achieving your goals‚Ä¶

A third of the time, you‚Äôll feel great.
A third of the time, you‚Äôll feel meh.
And a third of the time, you‚Äôll feel awful.

That‚Äôs not failure. That‚Äôs life.

Even @emmagrede, founding partner of SKIMS, cofounder & CEO of Good American, and host of @aspirewithemmagrede, has gone through what she calls the ‚ÄúRule of Thirds.‚Äù

The problem is, we‚Äôve been conditioned to think every day should feel amazing.

That if things aren‚Äôt going well, we‚Äôre doing something wrong.

But the truth is, the lows and the in-between days are part of the process too.

When you accept that, you stop fighting yourself. You stop quitting when it feels hard. And you stay in the game long enough to win.

This episode of @themelrobbinspodcast is the most motivational conversation I‚Äôve ever had. üéß ‚ÄúIf You Only Listen to One Podcast Today, Make It This One.‚Äù

posts.caption:
I've never liked the phrase "let it go." Whenever someone told me that, it felt like I had to lose, like I had to just roll over and be a doormat.

But saying "Let Them" is different.. 

When you say "Let Them," you rise above it and can see the situation for what it is.

And the part most people miss? Following it up with "Let Me."

That's where your real power is, not in changing them, but in choosing how you respond.

Listen to this full conversation with @jayshetty on The On Purpose Podcast (@jayshettypodcast) üéß "Mel Robbins: How to Use the ‚ÄòLet Them Theory‚Äô (A Life Changing Mindset Hack That 15 Million People Can‚Äôt Stop Talking About)"

It‚Äôs never too late to Chase your Dreams. Leave a ‚ÄúYes‚Äù if you agree üôè. 

You may have saw me post that my team won the North American Championship a couple months back but this was the moment I scored my first goal after not playing a game for years. 

In 2012 I played in my first game with @usateamhandball and I had the chance to play against @minikhoegh who was the greatest player ever from Greenland.

posts.caption:
Work is the #1 source of stress for most of us. 

Endless meetings. Unfair bosses. Rude customers. It all adds up fast.

But here‚Äôs the truth: when you let those things hijack your energy, you‚Äôve just handed your power to someone else.

That‚Äôs where the @letthemtheory comes in.

The next time your boss is in a bad mood, a coworker takes credit for your idea, or a customer snaps at you, try this:

Say to yourself, ‚ÄúLet Them.‚Äù 

Let Them be in a bad mood. 
Let Them gossip. 
Let Them be rude. 

Then shift to ‚ÄúLet Me.‚Äù

Let Me remind myself of what I can control: what I think, what I do (or don‚Äôt do), and how I process my emotions.

That‚Äôs the real power. Not in controlling or fixing other people, but in how you choose to respond.

Thank you, @jayshetty for having me on this episode of The On Purpose Podcast (@jayshettypodcast)! üéß ‚ÄúMel Robbins: How to Use the ‚ÄòLet Them Theory‚Äô (A Life Changing Mindset Hack That 15 Million People Can‚Äôt Stop Talking About)"

Season 7 of TO DINE FOR is now available on @pbs. In this episode - we dine at Barbara's favorite neighborhood spot @paolasosteria in NYC.

It‚Äôs how I picked up a camera in the first place, shooting skate videos with my friends. It‚Äôs not as cinematic as other stuff I try to put out, but it was never supposed to be. It was about pushing my abilities as a skateboarder during the countless sessions and endless fun we had skating this ramp. A real community was formed around it and I‚Äôm grateful to have been a part of it. Thank you @nahmias__ for everything and my boy @badmanbrooks for help filming and being my shred brother. Time for the next chapter. 

PS If you know skate culture I always loved ‚ÄúCheese & Crackers‚Äù and this is basically my version of it just less crazy. I call it ‚ÄúBandaids & Bearings.‚Äù üõπ

posts.caption:
Growing up my dream was to be a professional skateboarder. I put everything into making that dream a reality, but around age 18 I suffered a traumatic knee injury, forcing me to take a step back from skating and ultimately giving up my dream. Since then I haven‚Äôt felt like I‚Äôve progressed at all in my abilities and came to accept that my best skating days are probably behind me. Until I started skating this ramp around the corner from my house a few months ago. Now here I am 32 years young doing tricks that I couldn‚Äôt even do in my prime. 

It‚Äôs interesting how we‚Äôre conditioned to think our abilities peak in youth and inevitably decline with age, as if talent follows a strict timeline. I‚Äôve realized that being good at something isn‚Äôt just a phase, it‚Äôs a rhythm and sometimes it just takes the right beat to bring it back into motion. For me that beat was this ramp and I‚Äôm grateful for all the good times and progression it‚Äôs allowed. To anyone reading don‚Äôt hinder yourself by believing that you‚Äôre too old for something or will never be as good as you once were. Just search for the right spark, everything and more is within you. Working on a full mini ramp edit, but for now here‚Äôs a few tricks I‚Äôm proud of from the other day @nahmias__

There‚Äôs never been a lack of interested buyers to form a syndicate to buy this asset. It‚Äôs one of the most valuable media companies in America, 172 million users. What‚Äôs been missing until 48 hours ago was a seller, that‚Äôs Xi. ByteDance, that owns TikTok US, is controlled by the golden share held by Xi, so only he can decide its fate. 

Everybody wants a piece of this deal, believe me. The question is, under what terms? Because lawmakers have been all over the news today saying, Wait a second. We passed a law unanimously by the Supreme Court that says you can‚Äôt use the Chinese algorithm. So we make the assumption going into this deal that we‚Äôre gonna have to rewrite the code because of the penalty imposed by Congress, billions of dollars if you don‚Äôt abide by the law. So all of these moving parts are at play.

posts.caption:
Just because you‚Äôve failed doesn‚Äôt mean YOU are a failure. This is the requirement for success. Do you agree? 

It‚Äôs hard to remember this when people: 

- laugh at you when you make mistakes
- say ‚ÄúI told you so‚Äù
- talk about you behind your back 
- feel embarrassed being around you

No one likes being made fun of or feeling less than, but their feelings toward you is just a reflection of their lack of character. 

Failure is the prize not success. 

Because when you know we are all beginners at something and we never fully ‚Äúarrive‚Äù we can be ok with looking silly, making mistakes and not looking perfect all the time. 

You are a human being. Not a perfect human at all times. There‚Äôs a difference. 

This is my friendly reminder. Instead of beating yourself up when you fail‚Ä¶ celebrate yourself for staying consistent and having the courage to work through the mistakes when most of the world sits on their couch and criticizes those who go for their dreams. 

Make sure to get your tickets to SummitofGreatness.com for our live 2 day event in Los Angeles next weekend to hear from the biggest speakers in the world and continue your journey to living your dreams!

posts.caption:
It has always been hard for me to get out of bed. It just is what it is.

My husband @the.chrisrobbins just rolls right out of bed‚Ä¶ But not me, when the alarm goes off I just want to lay there like a human pot roast marinating in fear and dread.

Most mornings my 5 Second Rule works like a charm. I just count backwards 5-4-3-2-1 and then push myself to get out of bed‚Ä¶

But then there are those mornings that I can‚Äôt even muster up the energy to use my own damn rule.

On those mornings, I slither. It‚Äôs a really cool somatic method that my therapist @annedavinphd has me doing‚Ä¶ and this morning I needed it.

Here‚Äôs how you do it:

Literally just roll out of bed onto the floor, roll and writhe around just embodying that resistance that‚Äôs inside you and when you feel ready roll onto your hands and knees and start crawling toward the bathroom and at some point you‚Äôll feel ready to stand up and the resistance will be gone.

I know I know‚Ä¶ it‚Äôs super weird but boy does it work! Let me know if you‚Äôve tried it üëá

posts.caption:
Pablo Picasso said, ‚ÄúAll children are born artists. The problem is to remain an artist as we grow up.‚Äù

Those piano or guitar lessons you signed your kids up for‚Ä¶ Did you do that because you wish YOU stuck with your lessons as a kid?

You might‚Äôve given up something you loved as a kid, like music, art, dance, or writing, and then shoved that dream onto your kids instead.

I did this. I made all my kids take guitar lessons. Why? Because I‚Äôd always wanted to play, but I told myself the story that it was too late. Now, I have to be very clear - guitar lessons are what sparked our daughter @kendallrobbins LOVE of music and was a huge part of her journey to becoming a singer song writer, and our son @oakley_robbins is still taking lessons and playing and taking music theory in college. 

Phil‚Äôs point is important - sign them up yes, but do it WITH THEM. I‚Äôm happy to say - while I didn‚Äôt -> my husband did just that and learned to play too!  Some of my favorite memories of the kids when they were little was all four of them practicing guitar from the beginner books together. ü©µ

My takeaway is that I long to pick up an instrument and there‚Äôs something for me to explore personally - because when you Let your creative spirit come alive and allow your children to experience that side of you - it‚Äôs the single best form of inspiration for them - and a direct access to a deeper connection for you to yourself. Isn‚Äôt that beautiful?! 

If there‚Äôs something you miss, something that still stirs in you when you see someone else doing it‚Ä¶ That‚Äôs your sign. 

Pick it back up. Regardless, don‚Äôt wait.

This isn‚Äôt about being ‚Äúgood.‚Äù It‚Äôs about reconnecting with yourself. And when your kids see you do that, they learn that life doesn‚Äôt end when something ends. You can create a new beginning. 

In this new episode of @themelrobbinspodcast, musician and songwriter @philcookmusic is showing you how to unlock your creativity and reconnect with the part of yourself you‚Äôve been ignoring.

üéß ‚Äú4 Steps to Unlock Your Creativity & Feel More Inspired Every Day‚Äù

AI is creating unprecedented demand for power. Just in North America, the need is already 45 gigawatts, yet there are only five nuclear plants under construction. Nuclear is the future, but it‚Äôs 20 years away.

For now, the solution is stranded natural gas. It‚Äôs abundant, reliable, and can be deployed immediately while we build toward nuclear. Meanwhile, China is racing ahead with coal. This is why smart policy and private capital are essential, as pension funds, sovereign wealth funds, and private equity seek stable environments that deliver 11% to 17% returns. Energy is where those returns are.

Tariffs matter. Right now, Canada is facing a 35% tariff on softwood lumber and aluminum. That‚Äôs driving up the cost of housing in the U.S., because you can‚Äôt replace those inputs overnight‚Äîit would take decades. On top of that, Switzerland is staring at a 39% tariff on watches. As a collector, that one is killing me.

Policy should be reciprocal. Fifteen percent with Britain? Fine. But 35% with Canada and 39% with Switzerland? That‚Äôs not workable. These deals need to be fixed. The big trade wins are important, but the devil is in the details‚Äîand those details can cost consumers, businesses, and yes, even watch collectors like me.

172 million Americans are on TikTok, making it one of the most valuable platforms in the world. If the U.S. forces a takeover, you‚Äôre looking at a $30 to $40 billion deal. Buyers? Unlimited. Every private equity firm wants in. The real decision lies with President Xi, who holds a golden share. If he agrees, China can keep 20% ownership while 80% shifts into American hands.

But here is the catch... Congress and the Supreme Court have already deemed TikTok spyware. To stay in the U.S., the code must be rewritten from scratch, stripped of Chinese influence, and moved under American oversight. That is an 11 to 18 month process. If this deal closes, TikTok could emerge as a U.S. controlled powerhouse, creating jobs, and driving growth without the spyware baggage.

There‚Äôs a lot of speculation. They claimed earlier today that the Chinese didn‚Äôt actually understand what was on the table, the proposal to make TikTok compliant with the law. That would have ByteDance drop down to around 20%, and a new American ownership or a syndicate of American owners own the remainder. Now the Chinese were told through that description that maybe they are going to agree to that. But only Xi can decide and they will decide that on Friday.
